     It seems somewhat more likely though that one of the minor space-faring nations, or a completely new player in space, might have the greatest cost/benefit incentive for something as audacious as Orion. The US or Europe would benefit from an Orion, certainly, and so would the Chinese, but these entities are already in a dominant position in the human world. Brazil, Israel, India, and several others, all have it within their capability to build an Orion. Any of these could leapfrog the great powers and achieve world dominance by building an Orion, a status that is otherwise out of their reach. A consortium of two more of these nations is also likely, since this would allow for the pooling of resources that one may not have by itself.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/10/01 5:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Anybody with money could do it.</span><hr size=1> I think it's entirely possible a new player could surprise us. Not so much a nation but a wealthy group of nations or companies. I'd rule out the U.S having any involvement whatsoever.<br>
If I was a multibillionaire I could easily arrange it myself. Simply set up a new nation. Buy a few islands in the pacific or build them as Skase was planning to do (as a tax free haven for the corporate elite). Set it up as a Kingship with it's own laws and institutions. Like Tonga. As a new nation which hasn't signed ANY treaties with other nations it won't be subject to restraints on scientific research and development. <br>
Now I hire the starving nuclear physicists, engineers and other professionals I need from Russia to develop and build my Orion. We know it's possible so we are already halfway there when we start.<br>
Research into reactor rockets could go on alongside the pulse rocket development. Within a few years the scientists and engineers would have surpassed the achievements of the 60's and 70's. They would have better computers and other tools to work with from the very beginning.<br>
I think that any nation could build Orion. Atomic bombs are mid 1940's technology. That's 3 generations ago. India and Pakistan worked it out and I daresay many other nations have also but are keeping quiet about it. Reactor technology is common knowledge. Even 3rd world countries have access to that.<br>
The best thing about reactor rockets is that they woiuldnt break any international treaties. Abolutely anybody could commence another ROVER project.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/10/01 9:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Anybody with money could do it.</span><hr size=1> Bill Gates could afford it...    But who wants to be called a Microsoft-naut?    <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/10/01 11:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Bill Gates. Space Trillionaire.</span><hr size=1> I guarantee there is no way the american Government would let Billy reach space. They are chasing after him already because they think he is too rich. Imagine if he had access to all that lovely Platinum, Gold and other even more valuable heavy stuff sitting untouched in Asteroids out there. He would be God.<br>
<br>
Nope. The American government feels threatened enough already by Gates bank account. I'm surprised they haven't already assasinated him. Perhaps it's because he lost a lot of his money. <br>
<br>
I'm thinking the Arabs might be prepared to give it a go. They have the money. They don't mind a gamble. They are also greedy and power hungry. In fact I would be very surprised if we don't see Arab nuclear fleets in the next few decades. If we choose to ignore this technology then someone else is fully entitled to grab it and that serves us right. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/11/01 8:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Orion themed arms race?</span><hr size=1> If an Arab nation, or some other smaller country was the first to build and successfully launch a nuclear pulse rocket, that could trigger a massive space race ala sputnik...<br>
